<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="487" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[159,781,189,595]" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[159,286,444,467]" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BROWER" authorityYear="2010" box="[418,489,444,467]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Astraptes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boreas">
<emphasis box="[418,489,444,467]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">boreas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a masculine noun in apposition, is the personification of ‘the North Wind’. The species name alludes to the enthusiastic advocacy of DNA barcoding by Paul Hebert and his Canadian colleagues.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
